WEBVTT

00:13.520 --> 00:21.620
Cheetah presents The Happy Prince and The Selfish Giant by

00:21.620 --> 00:22.620
Oscar Wilde

00:39.060 --> 00:44.640
The Happy Prince Part 1 The Ruby

00:46.820 --> 00:50.680
On a tall column in the city there is a

00:50.680 --> 00:54.860
statue of the Happy Prince. He is covered

00:54.860 --> 01:01.680
with gold. He has two blue sapphires for eyes. On

01:01.680 --> 01:04.100
his sword there is a big red

01:04.100 --> 01:10.880
ruby. He is very beautiful. Everyone in the city likes

01:10.880 --> 01:12.320
the statue of the Happy

01:12.320 --> 01:18.980
Prince. Look at the Happy Prince! Says a mother to

01:18.980 --> 01:22.240
her little boy. He never cries.

01:22.240 --> 01:29.320
He is always happy. One night a little swallow flies

01:29.320 --> 01:31.960
over the city. His friends

01:31.960 --> 01:35.280
are in Egypt and he wants to go there too.

01:36.600 --> 01:39.380
He sees the statue on the tall column.

01:40.200 --> 01:45.920
Oh! What a beautiful statue! I have a golden bedroom.

01:47.080 --> 01:48.960
I can sleep here near the

01:48.960 --> 01:54.340
prince's feet. He says to himself. He puts his head

01:54.340 --> 01:58.160
under his wing. Suddenly a

01:58.160 --> 02:02.760
big drop of water falls on him. Then another drop

02:02.760 --> 02:06.780
falls. How strange. There

02:06.780 --> 02:12.400
aren't any clouds in the sky but it's raining. Another

02:12.400 --> 02:14.670
drop falls and the

02:14.670 --> 02:21.730
swallow looks up. The Happy Prince is crying. There are

02:21.730 --> 02:25.870
tears on his golden face. His face

02:25.870 --> 02:31.550
is very beautiful. The little swallow is sad. Who are

02:31.550 --> 02:34.970
you? He asks. I am the Happy

02:34.970 --> 02:40.950
Prince. Why are you crying? Asks the swallow. The people

02:40.950 --> 02:42.690
in the city call me the Happy

02:42.690 --> 02:47.930
Prince. In the castle I was happy. Everything there was

02:47.930 --> 02:51.270
beautiful. But now I am on this high

02:51.270 --> 02:54.750
column and I can see all the misery of my

02:54.750 --> 02:58.890
city. My heart is made of metal but I cry.

02:59.950 --> 03:04.510
Look! Over there there is a poor house. One of

03:04.510 --> 03:07.630
the windows is open. I can see a woman.

03:08.370 --> 03:12.430
She is very poor. There is a boy in bed.

03:13.350 --> 03:18.090
He is not well. He wants some oranges. His

03:18.090 --> 03:21.850
mother has nothing to give him except water. He is

03:21.850 --> 03:26.190
crying. Swallow, little swallow, can you

03:26.190 --> 03:29.550
take her the ruby from my sword? I must go

03:29.550 --> 03:33.030
to Egypt. Says the swallow. My friends are

03:33.030 --> 03:37.750
there. They fly up and down the Nile River. They

03:37.750 --> 03:40.850
talk to the flowers. They sleep in the

03:40.850 --> 03:46.770
tomb of the great king. Swallow, swallow, little swallow. Says

03:46.770 --> 03:49.030
the prince. Can you stay with

03:49.030 --> 03:52.890
me for one night and be my messenger? The boy

03:52.890 --> 04:03.010
is very ill and his mother is very sad. The

04:03.010 --> 04:07.850
boy is very cold here. He says. But I can

04:07.850 --> 04:11.130
stay with you for one night and be your messenger.

04:12.090 --> 04:17.890
Thank you, little swallow. Says the prince. The little swallow

04:17.890 --> 04:20.370
takes out the red ruby from

04:20.370 --> 04:24.610
the prince's sword. Then he flies away with the ruby.

04:25.690 --> 04:27.630
He flies over the houses of the

04:27.630 --> 04:33.030
city. He passes by the church and sees statues of

04:33.030 --> 04:37.310
white angels. He passes by the palace and

04:37.310 --> 04:43.970
hears lovely music. He flies over the river and sees

04:43.970 --> 04:57.610
the ships. At last he comes to the

04:57.610 --> 05:02.630
little swallow, puts the ruby on the table. Then he

05:02.630 --> 05:05.370
flies back to the happy prince and says,

05:06.070 --> 05:13.590
The night is cold. But I am warm now. Birds.

05:15.270 --> 05:18.750
There are about 9,000 types of birds in the

05:18.750 --> 05:19.090
world.

05:19.090 --> 05:26.070
All birds have feathers. Most birds have wings, but some

05:26.070 --> 05:30.190
birds can't fly. Let's look at some

05:30.190 --> 05:36.790
very interesting birds. Humming birds are the smallest birds in

05:36.790 --> 05:39.610
the world. They are about 5

05:39.610 --> 05:46.510
centimetres long. Humming birds can fly slowly or quickly, up,

05:46.890 --> 05:50.970
down or backwards. Eagles are

05:50.970 --> 05:57.290
big, strong birds. Many eagles live in the mountains. They

05:57.290 --> 06:01.490
fly high in the sky. Penguins are birds,

06:01.950 --> 06:07.950
but they can't fly. They swim. Penguins live in Antarctica.

06:10.170 --> 06:13.030
The ostrich is the biggest bird in the world.

06:14.190 --> 06:18.890
It is about 2.4 metres tall. It lives in

06:18.890 --> 06:24.490
central Africa. It can't fly, but it runs very fast.

06:27.330 --> 06:35.170
Part two, the sapphire. The next day the little swallow

06:35.170 --> 06:38.650
has a bath in the river. There is a

06:38.650 --> 06:44.370
professor walking over the bridge. What a strange thing. A

06:44.370 --> 06:47.350
swallow in winter. Says the professor.

06:48.090 --> 06:53.310
Tonight I go to Egypt. Says the swallow. So he

06:53.310 --> 06:55.750
visits the public monuments of the city.

06:57.230 --> 07:00.590
When the other winter birds see him, they are surprised

07:00.590 --> 07:04.550
and say, what a beautiful bird.

07:06.150 --> 07:12.010
This makes the little swallow very happy. In the evening,

07:12.490 --> 07:15.070
the swallow looks at the happy prince and

07:15.070 --> 07:21.110
says, I am going to Egypt. Swallow. Swallow. Little swallow.

07:21.630 --> 07:22.470
Says the prince.

07:23.250 --> 07:27.130
Can you stay with me another night? My friends are

07:27.130 --> 07:30.910
waiting for me in Egypt. Tomorrow they are

07:30.910 --> 07:34.970
flying up the river. They are visiting the statue of

07:34.970 --> 07:40.190
the god Memnon. At midday the yellow lions go

07:40.190 --> 07:44.410
to the water and drink. They have big green eyes

07:44.410 --> 07:45.810
and a terrible roar.

07:49.670 --> 07:54.550
Swallow. Swallow. Little swallow. Says the prince. I can see

07:54.550 --> 07:57.550
a young man in an attic. He is a writer.

07:58.530 --> 08:01.410
He can't write because he is too cold and hungry.

08:02.250 --> 08:06.670
Well, I can stay with you another night. Says

08:06.670 --> 08:11.390
the swallow. Must I take him another ruby? I haven't

08:11.390 --> 08:15.010
got a ruby. Says the prince. I only have my

08:15.010 --> 08:15.390
eyes.

08:16.250 --> 08:19.970
They are made of blue sapphires. Take one of the

08:19.970 --> 08:23.410
sapphires to him. He can sell it and buy food

08:23.410 --> 08:23.630
and

08:23.630 --> 08:29.330
firewood. Then he can finish his book. Dear prince. Says

08:29.330 --> 08:33.430
the swallow. I can't do that. The swallow

08:33.430 --> 08:40.130
begins to cry. Swallow. Swallow. Little swallow. Says the prince.

08:40.590 --> 08:41.750
Do as I say.

08:43.430 --> 08:47.630
So the swallow takes out the prince's eye and flies

08:47.630 --> 08:51.310
to the writer's attic. When the writer sees

08:51.310 --> 08:55.430
the sapphire on his desk he is very happy. Now

08:55.430 --> 08:58.690
I can finish my book. Says the young man.

08:59.890 --> 09:03.790
The next day the little swallow flies to the port.

09:04.630 --> 09:08.830
He looks at all the ships. In the evening he

09:08.830 --> 09:09.170
returns

09:09.170 --> 09:13.010
to the happy prince. I am here to say goodbye.

09:13.750 --> 09:19.330
He says. I am going to Egypt. Swallow. Swallow.

09:19.330 --> 09:23.950
Little swallow. Says the prince. Can you stay with me

09:23.950 --> 09:24.950
another night?

09:25.590 --> 09:30.450
It is winter and it is cold here. In Egypt

09:30.450 --> 09:35.110
the sun is warm. My friends are making a nest.

09:36.170 --> 09:41.390
Dear prince I must leave you. Next spring I can

09:41.390 --> 09:43.630
bring you a ruby and a sapphire.

09:44.570 --> 09:48.490
In the street below. Says the happy prince. There is

09:48.490 --> 09:50.630
a little match girl. Look.

09:51.630 --> 09:55.010
Her matches are falling in a puddle of water. Now

09:55.010 --> 10:00.310
she can't sell them. She is crying. She is poor

10:01.170 --> 10:06.690
and has no shoes. Take my other eye and give

10:06.690 --> 10:10.590
it to her. I can stay with you another night.

10:11.030 --> 10:14.610
Says the swallow. But I can't take out your other

10:14.610 --> 10:17.730
eye. Because then you can't see.

10:18.510 --> 10:23.410
Swallow. Swallow. Little swallow. Says the prince. Do as I

10:23.410 --> 10:23.790
say.

10:25.450 --> 10:30.310
So the swallow takes out the prince's other eye. He

10:30.310 --> 10:32.150
flies to the little match girl

10:32.150 --> 10:37.290
and puts the sapphire in her hand. What a lovely

10:37.290 --> 10:40.670
piece of glass. Says the little girl.

10:41.790 --> 10:47.010
She laughs and runs home. The swallow returns to the

10:47.010 --> 10:49.930
prince. You can't see now.

10:51.270 --> 10:56.070
I want to stay with you always. No little swallow.

10:56.610 --> 10:59.790
Says the poor prince. You must go to Egypt.

11:00.650 --> 11:05.770
I want to stay with you always. Says the swallow.

11:08.570 --> 11:11.870
Part three. The broken heart.

11:14.360 --> 11:19.480
The next day the swallow tells the prince stories about strange places.

11:20.520 --> 11:28.440
In Egypt there are red birds called ibises. They stand by the river Nile and catch fish.

11:29.480 --> 11:35.160
There is a sphinx too. It is very old and lives in a desert.

11:36.280 --> 11:44.040
It knows everything. There is a big green snake. It sleeps in a palm tree.

11:45.480 --> 11:50.920
Dear little swallow. Says the prince. You tell me about marvellous things.

11:51.720 --> 11:58.440
But misery is the biggest mystery. Fly over the city and tell me what you see.

11:59.080 --> 12:06.840
So the little swallow flies over the city. He sees rich people in beautiful houses.

12:07.880 --> 12:16.200
He sees poor people in dark streets. He sees hungry children with white faces.

12:17.640 --> 12:24.360
They are very cold. He flies back to the prince and tells him everything.

12:25.080 --> 12:31.480
I am covered with gold. Says the prince. You must take it off.

12:32.200 --> 12:39.160
Then we can give the gold to the poor. The swallow takes off the gold, leaf by leaf.

12:40.200 --> 12:45.720
He takes it to the poor. Now the prince looks dull and grey.

12:47.000 --> 12:52.120
The children's faces are happy. They laugh and play in the streets.

12:53.080 --> 12:55.080
We've got bread now!

12:55.880 --> 13:01.960
They say it is winter and it is very cold.

13:04.280 --> 13:10.120
There are some little boys skating on the ice. They are wearing red caps.

13:12.760 --> 13:19.160
The poor little swallow is very cold. He does not want to leave the prince.

13:20.120 --> 13:21.800
He loves him very much.

13:24.280 --> 13:28.920
Goodbye dear prince. I am dying.

13:30.120 --> 13:38.200
Says the poor little swallow. He kisses the happy prince and dies near his feet.

13:40.440 --> 13:45.080
At that moment there is a strange noise inside the statue.

13:45.960 --> 13:49.720
The prince's metal heart is breaking.

13:52.200 --> 13:54.760
It is certainly very cold.

13:57.240 --> 14:01.160
The next morning the mayor of the city looks at the statue.

14:02.440 --> 14:06.120
Dear me, the prince looks very ugly.

14:06.920 --> 14:09.800
Yes, he looks very bad.

14:10.600 --> 14:15.560
Say the mayor's friends. They always agree with the mayor.

14:17.080 --> 14:22.600
There is a dead bird near his feet. Birds must not die here.

14:24.600 --> 14:27.880
So they pull down the statue of the happy prince.

14:29.320 --> 14:35.080
They melt the statue in a furnace. But the broken heart does not melt.

14:35.800 --> 14:36.920
How strange.

14:37.480 --> 14:38.680
Says a worker.

14:38.680 --> 14:44.280
The broken heart does not melt in the furnace. We must throw it away.

14:46.280 --> 14:51.160
The worker takes the broken heart and puts it near the dead swallow.

14:52.520 --> 14:56.120
Bring me the two most precious things in the city.

14:57.240 --> 14:59.480
Says God to his angel.

15:00.200 --> 15:05.000
The angel brings him the broken heart and the dead bird.

15:06.200 --> 15:07.720
Very well.

15:07.720 --> 15:08.840
Says God.

15:08.840 --> 15:18.920
In my garden of paradise, this little bird can sing and the happy prince can live forever.

15:18.920 --> 15:29.880
Exercise six. Listen and circle the word you hear.

15:32.520 --> 15:36.120
There is a golden statue called the happy prince.

15:37.880 --> 15:41.720
A swallow stops near the statue to rest one night.

15:43.240 --> 15:46.440
He is going to Egypt because it is winter.

15:47.320 --> 15:53.000
The happy prince is crying because he can see the poor people in the city.

15:54.840 --> 15:57.960
The prince asks the swallow to help him.

15:59.480 --> 16:00.920
The swallow stays.

16:02.840 --> 16:06.200
He gives the poor people precious stones and gold.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.640
Now the prince is very dull.

16:11.960 --> 16:15.800
It's very cold and the swallow dies.

16:17.320 --> 16:19.480
The prince's heart breaks.

16:21.480 --> 16:26.360
The next day, the mayor of the city orders to pull down the statue.

16:28.440 --> 16:32.200
An angel brings God the bird and the heart.

16:34.600 --> 16:39.560
God says the prince and the swallow can live in paradise forever.

16:39.560 --> 16:44.840
Migratory Birds

16:46.440 --> 16:48.760
There are many migratory birds in the world.

16:49.720 --> 16:53.720
Swallows, ducks and stalks are migratory birds.

16:54.840 --> 16:57.000
They build their nests in the north.

16:58.440 --> 17:02.120
Every autumn, they fly long distances to the south.

17:03.400 --> 17:05.480
They fly together in big groups.

17:06.440 --> 17:10.200
In the south, it is warmer and there is more food.

17:11.560 --> 17:15.000
Every spring, they return to their nests in the north.

17:17.160 --> 17:24.520
Every year, Swallows leave San Juan Capistrano in California on the 23rd of October.

17:25.880 --> 17:27.800
They fly to South America.

17:29.000 --> 17:32.280
They always return on the 19th of March.

17:32.520 --> 17:38.840
In autumn, wild ducks leave Scandinavia and Siberia.

17:39.960 --> 17:41.800
They fly to Central Europe.

17:42.920 --> 17:45.000
They return home in the spring.

17:46.360 --> 17:49.240
In autumn, stalks leave Western Europe.

17:50.200 --> 17:51.960
They fly to Central Africa.

17:52.920 --> 17:54.920
They return home in the spring too.

17:54.920 --> 17:59.320
The Selfish Giant

18:00.680 --> 18:02.920
Part 1 Winter

18:05.400 --> 18:09.880
Every afternoon, the children play in the giant's garden.

18:11.400 --> 18:15.960
It is a big, lovely garden with green grass.

18:17.400 --> 18:19.560
Beautiful flowers grow there.

18:20.440 --> 18:26.200
There are 12 peach trees with delicate pink blossoms.

18:28.360 --> 18:32.840
The birds sit on the trees and sing sweet songs.

18:34.680 --> 18:36.840
The children listen to the birds.

18:38.360 --> 18:40.280
How happy we are here!

18:41.240 --> 18:42.520
The children say.

18:44.600 --> 18:46.040
The giant is away.

18:46.920 --> 18:50.520
He is visiting his friend, the ogre.

18:52.680 --> 18:56.680
After seven years, the giant returns home.

18:58.760 --> 19:02.840
When he arrives, he sees the children in his garden.

19:04.200 --> 19:05.080
They are playing.

19:12.280 --> 19:14.360
What are you doing here?

19:15.320 --> 19:17.560
He says in a loud voice.

19:19.320 --> 19:23.000
The children are very scared and run away.

19:23.720 --> 19:28.120
This is my garden, my garden.

19:28.120 --> 19:29.240
Says the giant.

19:30.360 --> 19:32.760
Only I can play here.

19:34.680 --> 19:38.840
So the giant builds a high wall around the garden.

19:40.200 --> 19:42.280
Then he puts up a sign.

19:44.360 --> 19:51.880
No one must enter.

19:53.640 --> 19:56.520
He is a very selfish giant.

19:58.920 --> 20:02.840
Now the poor children have no place to play.

20:04.600 --> 20:06.600
They can't play on the road.

20:07.720 --> 20:12.920
There are big stones on the road and the children don't like them.

20:13.720 --> 20:18.600
After school, the children walk near the high wall.

20:20.040 --> 20:23.720
They talk about the beautiful garden inside.

20:26.520 --> 20:32.520
It is spring and there are little blossoms and little birds everywhere.

20:34.680 --> 20:39.960
But in the garden of the selfish giant, it is still winter.

20:39.960 --> 20:46.040
The birds do not sing there because there are no children.

20:47.560 --> 20:49.720
There are no blossoms on the trees.

20:52.440 --> 20:56.360
A beautiful flower puts its head out of the grass.

20:57.720 --> 20:59.160
It looks for the children.

21:00.920 --> 21:05.160
It sees the sign and goes back into the ground.

21:06.920 --> 21:08.120
It goes to sleep.

21:10.920 --> 21:14.440
Only the snow and the frost are happy.

21:16.360 --> 21:20.120
Spring doesn't come to this garden.

21:21.080 --> 21:26.680
They say, we can live here all year.

21:29.640 --> 21:34.520
The snow covers the grass with her big white cloak.

21:35.960 --> 21:39.080
The frost paints the trees silver.

21:40.760 --> 21:46.200
The snow and the frost invite the North Wind to stay with them.

21:47.400 --> 21:51.880
The North Wind comes and blows all day in the garden.

21:53.800 --> 21:57.560
He has a big warm coat and a hat.

22:01.560 --> 22:04.360
This is a wonderful place.

22:05.640 --> 22:07.800
Says the North Wind.

22:07.800 --> 22:10.440
We must invite the hail.

22:12.600 --> 22:14.280
So the hail comes.

22:15.640 --> 22:17.320
He is dressed in grain.

22:18.920 --> 22:22.360
For three days he runs around the garden.

22:23.800 --> 22:25.800
Then he dances on the roof.

22:27.320 --> 22:28.920
There is a lot of hail.

22:31.720 --> 22:34.200
Why doesn't the spring come?

22:35.160 --> 22:37.320
Asks the selfish giant.

22:38.920 --> 22:44.600
He sits at the window and looks at his cold white garden.

22:46.920 --> 22:51.320
The spring never comes and the summer never comes.

22:53.000 --> 22:56.120
The autumn gives fruit to all gardens.

22:57.480 --> 23:02.040
But it doesn't give any fruit to the selfish giant's garden.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.080
He is too selfish.

23:05.720 --> 23:07.000
The autumn says.

23:09.080 --> 23:12.120
So it is always winter there.

23:13.720 --> 23:21.800
The North Wind, the hail, the frost and the snow live in the selfish giant's garden.

23:24.840 --> 23:27.320
Part two, spring.

23:28.120 --> 23:32.200
One morning, the giant hears some lovely music.

23:33.000 --> 23:35.640
Oh, it must be the king's musicians.

23:42.280 --> 23:43.640
Says the giant.

23:45.640 --> 23:49.080
A little bird is singing a lovely song.

23:50.120 --> 23:52.520
The hail stops dancing on the roof.

23:52.680 --> 23:54.600
The North Wind stops blowing.

23:55.560 --> 23:58.040
There is a sweet perfume in the air.

24:00.200 --> 24:03.400
I think spring is here at last.

24:04.440 --> 24:05.640
Says the giant.

24:06.840 --> 24:10.040
He goes to the window and looks outside.

24:12.040 --> 24:14.040
What does he see?

24:15.880 --> 24:18.440
He sees something wonderful.

24:19.240 --> 24:22.040
There is a little hole in the wall.

24:23.320 --> 24:26.280
Now the children can enter the garden.

24:27.560 --> 24:30.760
There is a little child on every tree.

24:32.200 --> 24:34.760
The trees have beautiful blossoms.

24:35.800 --> 24:38.520
They are very happy to have the children.

24:40.040 --> 24:42.600
The birds are flying in the sky

24:42.600 --> 24:44.600
and singing the birds.

24:45.160 --> 24:48.600
The birds are flying in the sky and singing.

24:51.080 --> 24:52.680
The flowers are laughing.

24:54.040 --> 24:56.200
There is happiness in the garden.

24:58.920 --> 25:02.680
But it is still winter in one corner of the garden.

25:04.360 --> 25:07.480
In that corner, there is a little boy.

25:09.080 --> 25:13.000
He is very small and he can't climb the tree.

25:14.920 --> 25:17.960
He is walking around the tree and crying.

25:19.640 --> 25:21.400
The tree is covered with snow.

25:22.600 --> 25:24.360
The North Wind is blowing.

25:25.720 --> 25:27.480
Climb up, little boy.

25:28.600 --> 25:29.400
Says the tree.

25:30.840 --> 25:32.760
But the boy is too small.

25:35.160 --> 25:39.800
When he sees the little boy, the giant's heart melts.

25:41.240 --> 25:43.400
I am very selfish.

25:43.880 --> 25:44.520
He says.

25:45.160 --> 25:48.600
Now I know why the spring does not come here.

25:49.480 --> 25:52.440
I must put that little boy on the tree.

25:53.240 --> 25:55.640
Then I must knock down the wall.

25:56.440 --> 26:00.520
My garden must be the children's playground forever.

26:02.520 --> 26:07.000
The giant opens his door and goes out into the garden.

26:08.920 --> 26:12.280
When the children see the giant, they are afraid.

26:13.400 --> 26:14.200
They run away.

26:18.520 --> 26:20.600
The winter returns to the garden.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.320
The little boy does not run away.

26:26.520 --> 26:27.480
He is crying.

26:29.240 --> 26:35.480
The giant takes him in his big hand and puts him on a branch of the tree.

26:37.320 --> 26:39.960
Suddenly, there are blossoms on the tree.

26:41.160 --> 26:42.840
The birds come and sing.

26:44.200 --> 26:46.520
The little boy is very happy.

26:47.560 --> 26:49.080
He kisses the giant.

26:51.160 --> 26:54.920
When the children see this, they come back to the garden.

26:56.040 --> 26:57.720
The spring comes back too.

26:59.080 --> 27:02.440
It is your garden now, little children.

27:02.440 --> 27:03.480
Says the giant.

27:04.680 --> 27:09.480
He takes a big axe and knocks down the wall.

27:14.360 --> 27:15.960
Exercise four.

27:15.960 --> 27:21.240
Listen to part of the text again and fill in the missing words.

27:22.520 --> 27:25.800
I think spring is here at last.

27:26.520 --> 27:27.800
Says the giant.

27:28.760 --> 27:32.600
He goes to the window and looks outside.

27:34.040 --> 27:35.720
What does he see?

27:37.160 --> 27:39.640
He sees something wonderful.

27:40.360 --> 27:42.680
There is a little hole in the wall.

27:43.960 --> 27:46.760
Now the children can enter the garden.

27:47.960 --> 27:50.760
There is a little child on every tree.

27:51.800 --> 27:55.000
The trees have beautiful blossoms.

27:56.200 --> 27:58.840
They are very happy to have the children.

28:00.040 --> 28:03.560
The birds are flying in the sky and singing.

28:04.840 --> 28:06.840
The flowers are laughing.

28:07.240 --> 28:09.080
The flowers are laughing.

28:10.440 --> 28:12.760
There is happiness in the garden.

28:16.040 --> 28:16.760
Part three.

28:18.360 --> 28:19.480
White blossoms.

28:21.480 --> 28:24.600
At 12 o'clock, people go to the market.

28:28.120 --> 28:32.440
They see the giant playing with the children in the beautiful garden.

28:32.440 --> 28:37.960
The children play all day.

28:39.720 --> 28:43.160
In the evening, they say goodbye to the giant.

28:44.120 --> 28:45.960
Where is the little boy?

28:46.760 --> 28:47.880
Asks the giant.

28:49.480 --> 28:50.680
We don't know.

28:51.960 --> 28:53.080
Answer the children.

28:54.200 --> 28:57.000
You must tell him to come tomorrow.

28:58.120 --> 28:59.080
Says the giant.

28:59.960 --> 29:02.120
We don't know where he lives.

29:03.400 --> 29:04.600
Say the children.

29:05.960 --> 29:09.160
The giant is very sad and says,

29:10.040 --> 29:14.440
He is my little friend and I want to see him.

29:16.840 --> 29:21.480
Every afternoon, after school, the children play with the giant.

29:22.680 --> 29:25.400
The giant is very kind to the children.

29:25.720 --> 29:30.920
But he wants to see his first little friend.

29:34.440 --> 29:35.880
Where is he?

29:36.520 --> 29:37.960
He says to himself.

29:40.280 --> 29:43.880
Many years pass and the giant grows old.

29:45.160 --> 29:47.000
He can't play with the children.

29:48.040 --> 29:54.360
So he sits in an enormous armchair and watches the children play.

29:55.880 --> 29:58.440
He looks at his garden and says,

29:59.320 --> 30:07.560
I have many beautiful flowers, but the children are the most beautiful flowers of all.

30:09.960 --> 30:14.360
One winter morning, the giant looks out of his window.

30:15.880 --> 30:18.040
He does not hate the winter now.

30:19.000 --> 30:23.880
He knows that the spring is sleeping and that the flowers are resting.

30:26.040 --> 30:29.000
Suddenly, he sees something marvellous.

30:30.440 --> 30:32.120
He looks and looks.

30:33.320 --> 30:35.000
He is very surprised.

30:36.600 --> 30:42.360
In a corner of the garden, there is a tree with lovely white blossoms.

30:43.880 --> 30:48.520
Its branches are golden and there is silver fruit on them.

30:50.280 --> 30:53.160
Under this tree, there is a little boy.

30:54.120 --> 30:57.080
It is the giant's little friend.

30:58.840 --> 31:01.000
The giant runs to the garden.

31:01.720 --> 31:03.160
He is very happy.

31:04.360 --> 31:08.760
He runs across the green grass and goes to the child.

31:11.240 --> 31:15.000
When he is near the child, he becomes angry.

31:16.360 --> 31:16.920
He says,

31:18.440 --> 31:20.120
What are these wounds?

31:20.760 --> 31:24.760
There are the marks of two nails on the child's hands and feet.

31:25.800 --> 31:27.240
What are these wounds?

31:27.240 --> 31:28.600
He says the giant.

31:29.800 --> 31:31.560
These are the wounds of love.

31:32.520 --> 31:34.040
He says the child.

31:35.240 --> 31:36.440
Who are you?

31:37.480 --> 31:39.480
He asks the giant.

31:40.680 --> 31:43.880
The giant has a strange sensation.

31:44.840 --> 31:47.640
He kneels in front of the little child.

31:47.640 --> 31:51.560
The child smiles at the giant and says,

31:51.560 --> 31:54.120
You let me play in your garden.

31:55.320 --> 31:59.080
Today, you can come with me to my garden.

32:00.040 --> 32:02.040
It is paradise.

32:03.800 --> 32:06.360
When the children come to the garden,

32:06.360 --> 32:09.800
they find the giant dead under a tree.

32:10.680 --> 32:14.200
He is covered with white blossoms.

32:15.160 --> 32:18.040
He is covered with white blossoms.

32:21.720 --> 32:22.440
Gardens

32:25.480 --> 32:27.880
A garden is a beautiful place.

32:29.400 --> 32:31.080
Children play in gardens.

32:32.840 --> 32:34.280
Trees, bushes,

32:34.840 --> 32:37.480
grass and flowers are part of a garden.

32:39.240 --> 32:41.080
Birds, butterflies,

32:41.720 --> 32:45.000
insects and other little animals live there.

32:46.920 --> 32:48.440
Some gardens are small.

32:49.800 --> 32:51.080
Others are big.

32:52.920 --> 32:57.480
Palaces and castles usually have enormous gardens.

32:59.880 --> 33:02.280
Italian villas and palaces

33:02.280 --> 33:05.880
have beautiful gardens with statues and fountains.

33:06.040 --> 33:12.440
The Bobbi Gardens in Florence, Italy are a splendid example.

33:14.440 --> 33:18.680
In France and in England, there are many lovely gardens.

33:20.680 --> 33:24.440
The gardens of the castles of the Loire Valley in France

33:25.240 --> 33:27.320
and Hampton Court in England.

33:30.200 --> 33:35.080
Most American and British people have a flower or vegetable garden.

33:36.440 --> 33:39.880
They often have parties or barbecues in their gardens.

33:43.480 --> 33:45.320
Have you got green fingers?

33:47.960 --> 33:49.880
Let's plant an avocado stone.

33:50.840 --> 33:53.880
Silen, you can have an avocado plant.

33:54.680 --> 33:55.640
It's very easy.

33:57.640 --> 34:01.480
One, take an avocado stone and wash it.

34:01.480 --> 34:06.920
Two, put three toothpicks in the stone.

34:07.960 --> 34:10.600
Put half of it in a glass of water.

34:11.960 --> 34:15.880
Three, put it near a window inside your house.

34:17.560 --> 34:21.080
Four, change the water every week.

34:23.480 --> 34:29.560
Five, when you see the first roots, put the stone in a pot of earth.

34:29.800 --> 34:35.320
Six, keep the pot inside your house.

34:36.120 --> 34:39.160
Remember to water it every week.

